## Subset manifest

All 7 files from `Sources/MessagePack/` are included verbatim:

  MessagePack.swift           — MessagePackValue enum, Equatable, Hashable,
                                MessagePackError
  Pack.swift                  — pack(_:) top-level function
  Unpack.swift                — unpack(_:compatibility:), unpackFirst,
                                unpackAll, unpackArray, unpackMap
  Subdata.swift               — Subdata RandomAccessCollection view over Data
  LiteralConvertibles.swift   — ExpressibleBy* conformances
  ConvenienceInitializers.swift — init overloads for all types
  ConvenienceProperties.swift — typed accessor computed properties

## MoonSwift vendor modifications (Swift 6 strict-concurrency compliance)

The upstream code predates Swift 6. The following minimal surgical edits were
applied; each is marked with `// MoonSwift vendor note:` in the source:

1. `MessagePack.swift`: added `: Sendable` to the `MessagePackValue` enum
   declaration. All associated values (Bool, Int64, UInt64, Float, Double,
   String, Data, [MessagePackValue], [MessagePackValue: MessagePackValue],
   (Int8, Data)) are themselves Sendable, so this is a semantically correct
   conformance, not a suppression.

2. `Subdata.swift`: added `: Sendable` to the `Subdata` struct declaration.
   All stored properties (base: Data, baseStartIndex: Int, baseEndIndex: Int)
   are Sendable value types, so this is a semantically correct conformance.

No other edits were made. The msgpack wire format encoded and decoded by
these files is identical to upstream.

## Upgrade policy

To upgrade: fetch the new upstream commit, overwrite these 7 files, re-apply
the two `: Sendable` additions, update this NOTICE. Verify round-trip tests
remain green.

